reagent-name-electrolytic-nanites = electrolytic nanites
reagent-desc-electrolytic-nanites = Nanomachines programmed to identify points of corrosive damage in silicons and perform rapid repairs via electrolysis.

reagent-name-crystal-lattice-nanites = crystal lattice nanites
reagent-desc-crystal-lattice-nanites = Nanomachines capable of repairing the molecular damage caused to silicons by exposure to radiation.

reagent-name-optical-fiber-nanites = optical fiber nanites
reagent-desc-optical-fiber-nanites = Able to repair damage to the visual receptors of silicons without requiring replacement of the glass itself.

reagent-name-rescue-nanites = rescue nanites
reagent-desc-rescue-nanites = Activate when introduced to a silicon body in critical condition, rapidly repairing damaged components. Injecting too many at once can lead to internal damage.

reagent-name-reconstructor-nanites = reconstructor nanites
reagent-desc-reconstructor-nanites = Tiny little triumphs of Cybersun nanoengineering, able to fix nearly any kind of injury a silicon can sustain.

reagent-name-overclock-nanites = overclock nanites
reagent-desc-overclock-nanites = These nanites are designed to interface with positronic brains, massively increasing their processing speeds and granting minor regenerative abilities.
